<div id="banner">
	<h1>How to Do Stuff</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>I’m proud to introduce my new series: <a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/2002/howto/">How to Do Stuff</a>. It currently features two articles:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/2002/howto/cvs">How to Do Version Control with CVS</a></li>
  <li><a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/2002/howto/stream">How to Do Live Streaming</a></li>
</ul>

<p>I’m especially proud of <a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/2002/howto/stream">How to Do Live Streaming</a>. It covers how to do broadcasting, reflection, encoding, recording, etc., all using pipes of small Unix tools.</p>

<p>The whole section is written using <a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/2002/atx/">my humane structured text format, atx</a>. You can see the source code of a page by adding <code>.atx</code> to the end.</p>

<p>(These Movable Type entries are also written in atx. I wrote a small Movable Type plugin to pass the entries through my atx converter before publishing.)</p>

<p class="posted">posted March 17, 2003 11:10 AM (<a class="category" href="cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000866" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

